I’m currently putting together a study to look at the effects of BB emissions on ENSO. To do this I’ll need a set of emissions that “typical” of a strong El Niño and a set that are typical of a strong La Niña - perhaps a 3 yr record where yrs 2/3 are roughly climatological. 

Does a best approach for doing this come to mind? For example I’m thinking of merely averaging together the observed 1997/98 and 2015/16 years for El Niño, and 1998/1999 and 2010/11 years for La Niña?

Interested in being involved in the work?

